This paper discusses the security and privacy concerns related to machine learning models deployed on cloud platforms, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper specifically focuses on machine learning as a service (MLaaS) platforms, which involves the use of machine learning algorithms and techniques (cs.LG). The techniques presented in the paper involve monitoring and analyzing query and response streams, which is related to data mining and analysis (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the potential impact on software engineering practices, such as the need for model owners to be aware of possible extraction attacks (cs.SE). Finally, the paper involves the use of datasets and databases, which is related to database systems (cs.DB).
